Sentencas: Copper coated nickel foam with Cu/Ni ratio of 2.5 was fabricated using electrochemical plating and characterized using XRD, SEM, EDS and Van der Pauw four point conductivity measurements.
Titulo: Copper coated nickel foam as current collector for H2S-containing syngas solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Copper coated nickel foam exhibited good stability of electronic conductivity and mechanical strength during more than 150 h exposure to 500 ppm H2S-containing syngas at 750 degrees C.
Titulo: Copper coated nickel foam as current collector for H2S-containing syngas solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In contrast, uncoated nickel foam readily underwent severe carbon deposition and brittle fracture resulting in dramatic increase of electronic resistance under the same testing conditions.
Titulo: Copper coated nickel foam as current collector for H2S-containing syngas solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Copper coated nickel foam is a promising current collector for H2S-containing syngas solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Copper coated nickel foam as current collector for H2S-containing syngas solid oxide fuel cells
